

Linux Collection Script
-----------------------

This Script will collect the following data from Linux servers

Name
CPUs
Cores
Network Cards  
Open Network Ports
Disks


Instructions
---------------
Add the desired servers IP addresses to ips.txt, one IP per line


Syntax: iv.sh [username]

The Output will be displyed on the screen as well as in files on the `output` folder
In the `output` folder, each server will have it's own file stating the server ip and a timestamp

Assumptions:
---------------------
- Authentication keys are available for password-less SSH login
- Hosts are Linux Only
- Hosts IP's are available on the ips.txt file

*** Running collect.sh will grab and display data from your local machine